 getting ready for this, what would I say?

61
00:03:06,860 --> 00:03:09,040
 Like, what would God have me say?

62
00:03:09,040 --> 00:03:11,600
 But more of like when I was in my 20s,

63
00:03:11,600 --> 00:03:14,240
 and 30s for that matter, based on the hair,

64
00:03:14,240 --> 00:03:15,820
 I'm definitely out of that zone.

65
00:03:15,820 --> 00:03:18,840
 But a lot of times at Passion Conference, I wear a hat,

66
00:03:18,840 --> 00:03:21,280
 so people may think I'm a little younger than I really am.

67
00:03:21,280 --> 00:03:22,600
 I didn't lose my hair so quickly.

68
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:26,440
 But anyway, moving on from that, what would I tell myself?

69
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:28,260
 'Cause I was living in Arlington, Texas.

70
00:03:28,260 --> 00:03:30,720
 We got any Arlington people in the house?

71
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:35,720
 Come on, when I was 24, 25, 26, I was living in Arlington,

72
00:03:35,720 --> 00:03:39,560
 and some of you in here have all of life figured out,

73
00:03:39,560 --> 00:03:42,920
 and you're on a path, and you're feeling good,

74
00:03:42,920 --> 00:03:44,880
 and you know where you're going,

75
00:03:44,880 --> 00:03:48,160
 you know what you're aiming for, everything's sorted,

76
00:03:48,160 --> 00:03:49,760
 and if that's you, don't raise your hand,

77
00:03:49,760 --> 00:03:53,160
 because that's really gonna frustrate the rest of us.

78
00:03:53,160 --> 00:03:56,880
 But when I was 24, 25, 26, living in Arlington,

79
00:03:56,880 --> 00:04:00,400
 I felt a lot of pressure to figure out

80
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:03,320
 what my life was supposed to be about.

81
00:04:03,320 --> 00:04:06,460
 And it was the decisions that,

82
00:04:06,460 --> 00:04:08,640
 and at the time, I was following the Lord,

83
00:04:08,640 --> 00:04:09,960
 I was working at a church,

84
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:12,400
 I was wanting my life to be for God's glory,

85
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:17,360
 but I was just like, man, I felt so much pressure,

86
00:04:17,360 --> 00:04:22,120
 like a dating decision, a career decision,

87
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:24,880
 a vacation decision, a lunch decision,

88
00:04:24,880 --> 00:04:27,660
 it was just like, man, I wanna get it right,

89
00:04:27,660 --> 00:04:30,800
 I know this is supposed to be the greatest time of my life,

90
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:33,000
 and I got my whole life in front of me, God willing,

91
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:36,280
 but I don't wanna mess up.

92
00:04:36,280 --> 00:04:39,540
 So I was like, what would I tell myself

93
00:04:39,540 --> 00:04:41,320
 looking back on that season of life?

94
00:04:41,320 --> 00:04:43,780
 That's part of what I was gonna bring.

95
00:04:43,780 --> 00:04:45,960
 And then I had some young professionals at my house

96
00:04:45,960 --> 00:04:50,440
 on Monday night, I think that was Monday night,

97
00:04:50,440 --> 00:04:52,440
 no, I'm sorry, it was Thursday night,

98
00:04:52,440 --> 00:04:56,640
 and I was talking to a close friend of ours,

99
00:04:56,640 --> 00:04:59,980
 it's in your season, a lot of you season of life,

100
00:04:59,980 --> 00:05:04,520
 and just talking to him, and I felt the pressure,

101
00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:05,920
 like that was on his,

102
00:05:05,920 --> 00:05:09,440
 I could see the pressure on his shoulders,

103
00:05:09,440 --> 00:05:12,600
 like physically, and he was just like,

104
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:16,040
 I'm trying to figure life out, and I need some help,

105
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:19,040
 and Brad and Brittany, my wife,

106
00:05:19,040 --> 00:05:22,600
 would you help me make some of these decisions?

107
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:26,180
 And so I pray that God would use our time together,

108
00:05:26,180 --> 00:05:30,000
 and the moments I have with you to encourage you.

109
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:33,060
 We're gonna be in John chapter 13.

110
00:05:33,060 --> 00:05:38,420
 We're going to a very familiar passage,

111
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:43,040
 and if we're not too careful with scripture,

112
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:46,200
 and with Jesus, and church, and the porch,

113
00:05:46,200 --> 00:05:49,480
 we get too familiar, can I get a amen?

114
00:05:49,480 --> 00:05:52,200
 Familiarity breeds contempt.

115
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:55,920
 It's like, we got any golfers in the house?

116
00:05:55,920 --> 00:05:59,720
 Any public golf course people in the house

117
00:05:59,720 --> 00:06:02,480
 that you just hope when you go play golf

118
00:06:02,480 --> 00:06:04,520
 that there's actually grass,

119
00:06:04,520 --> 00:06:06,200
 and you gotta make a decision,

120
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:09,160
 is do you wanna pay the extra $15

121
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:12,280
 to get a bucket of golf balls to hit off the range?

122
00:06:12,280 --> 00:06:15,640
 Yesterday, I got to go and played a really nice country club,

123
00:06:15,640 --> 00:06:17,220
 and I was giddy about it.

124
00:06:17,220 --> 00:06:20,060
 I'm a terrible golfer, but when I got there,

125
00:06:20,060 --> 00:06:21,600
 the greens were perfect.

126
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:24,480
 Somebody came and got my bag out of the car.

127
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:28,180
 They put it on a golf cart, like were taking care of me.

128
00:06:28,180 --> 00:06:30,040
 They like took it to the range.

129
00:06:30,040 --> 00:06:31,480
 There was like Pro V1.

130
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:33,000
 If you're not a golfer, just follow me.

131
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:36,520
 Pro V1 golf balls laid out on this range.

132
00:06:36,520 --> 00:06:38,400
 The range was perfect.

133
00:06:38,400 --> 00:06:40,560
 The key boxes were perfect.

134
00:06:40,560 --> 00:06:41,800
 The greens were perfect.

135
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:44,600
 Even in Dallas, Texas, where it can be hard to grow grass.

136
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:47,200
 I'm like, this is incredible.

137
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:48,900
 We only played nine holes.

138
00:06:48,900 --> 00:06:52,960
 I was like, and it was, yes, 45 degrees and windy,

139
00:06:52,960 --> 00:06:55,700
 but I'm like, I don't get to play here ever.

140
00:06:55,700 --> 00:06:57,700
 I go back to the public golf courses

141
00:06:57,700 --> 00:07:00,680
 where there's not a lot of grass most days,

142
00:07:00,680 --> 00:07:02,260
 but these guys played all the time.

143
00:07:02,260 --> 00:07:04,860
 So they're like, man, should we even play?

144
00:07:04,860 --> 00:07:06,640
 I'm like, yes.

145
00:07:06,640 --> 00:07:08,400
 I'm not familiar with this.

146
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:10,240
 This isn't normal for me.

147
00:07:10,240 --> 00:07:14,160
 Don't rob me of this experience.

148
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:15,840
 But a lot of times, if we're not careful

149
00:07:15,840 --> 00:07:19,600
 when we approach scripture, when we approach Jesus,

150
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:23,600
 we're just too familiar, too flippant.

151
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:27,780
 Oh, I've been there, heard that.

152
00:07:27,780 --> 00:07:29,920
 Know what that's all about.

153
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:33,500
 And I was reading John chapter 13 a couple months ago,

154
00:07:33,500 --> 00:07:36,840
 and it's the night before Jesus would give his life on a cross

155
00:07:36,840 --> 00:07:38,560
 just before the Passover meal,

156
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:41,360
 the last hours of his life on earth.

157
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:46,100
 And it's the story of Jesus washing his,

158
00:07:46,100 --> 00:07:48,640
 what is it?

159
00:07:48,640 --> 00:07:51,080
 Washing his disciples' feet.

160
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:53,320
 You're familiar with the story.

161
00:07:53,320 --> 00:07:54,720
 Good job right there.

162
00:07:54,720 --> 00:07:58,440
 And we know, I think the point of it

163
00:07:58,440 --> 00:08:01,000
 is that we should go and do likewise.

164
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:05,000
 And this was one of the most significant acts

165
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:07,120
 of Jesus's life.

166
00:08:07,120 --> 00:08:11,000
 And one of the most successful, honestly, 24 hours,

167
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:13,320
 the most successful 24 hours of anybody

168
00:08:13,320 --> 00:08:15,080
 that's ever walked on planet earth.

169
00:08:15,080 --> 00:08:18,960
 But when I was reading John chapter 13,

170
00:08:18,960 --> 00:08:22,120
 it hit me in a brand new way.

171
00:08:22,120 --> 00:08:23,840
 Let's dig in.

172
00:08:23,840 --> 00:08:25,200
 John 13, verse one.

173
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:29,000
 It was just before the Passover festival.

174
00:08:29,980 --> 00:08:34,980
 Jesus knew, I want you to see that word knew, K-N-E-W.

175
00:08:34,980 --> 00:08:39,920
 Jesus knew that the hour had come

176
00:08:39,920 --> 00:08:43,560
 for him to leave this world and go to the Father.

177
00:08:43,560 --> 00:08:45,860
 Having loved his own who were in the world,

178
00:08:45,860 --> 00:08:48,120
 he loved them to the end.

179
00:08:48,120 --> 00:08:51,320
 The evening meal was in progress

180
00:08:51,320 --> 00:08:53,920
 and the devil had already prompted Judas,

181
00:08:53,920 --> 00:08:58,280
 the son of Simon Iscariot, to betray Jesus.

182
00:08:58,280 --> 00:09:03,180
 Jesus knew that the Father had put all things

183
00:09:03,180 --> 00:09:07,080
 under his power and that he also knew

184
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:11,620
 that he had come from God and was returning to God.

185
00:09:11,620 --> 00:09:15,940
 So he got up from the meal, took off his outer clothing

186
00:09:15,940 --> 00:09:18,520
 and wrapped a towel around his waist.

187
00:09:18,520 --> 00:09:20,620
 After that, he poured out water into a basin,

188
00:09:20,620 --> 00:09:22,420
 began to wash his disciples' feet,

189
00:09:22,420 --> 00:09:24,940
 drying them with the towel that was wrapped around him,

190
00:09:24,940 --> 00:09:28,400
 a very selfless act.

191
00:09:28,400 --> 00:09:31,940
 Something of Jesus's stature in this culture

192
00:09:31,940 --> 00:09:34,060
 would not have been done.

193
00:09:34,060 --> 00:09:35,580
 He came to Simon Peter, who said to him,

194
00:09:35,580 --> 00:09:39,620
 "Lord, are you going to wash my feet?"

195
00:09:39,620 --> 00:09:44,100
 Jesus replied, "You do not realize now what I am doing,

196
00:09:44,100 --> 00:09:47,220
 "but later you will understand."

197
00:09:47,220 --> 00:09:51,300
 "But no," said Peter, "you shall never wash my feet."

198
00:09:52,500 --> 00:09:55,180
 Jesus answered, "Unless I wash you,

199
00:09:55,180 --> 00:09:56,920
 "you have no part with me."

200
00:09:56,920 --> 00:10:02,260
 Then Lord Simon Peter replied, "Not just my feet,

201
00:10:02,260 --> 00:10:04,380
 "wash my hands, wash my head as well."

202
00:10:04,380 --> 00:10:06,840
 Jesus answered, "Those who have had a bath

203
00:10:06,840 --> 00:10:08,100
 "need only to wash their feet.

204
00:10:08,100 --> 00:10:09,700
 "Their whole body is clean.

205
00:10:09,700 --> 00:10:12,660
 "And you are clean, though not every one of you."

206
00:10:12,660 --> 00:10:14,460
 For he knew he was going to betray him

207
00:10:14,460 --> 00:10:17,420
 and that's why he said not everyone was clean.

208
00:10:17,420 --> 00:10:18,980
 When he finished washing their feet,

209
00:10:18,980 --> 00:10:21,980
 he put on his clothes, returned to his place.

210
00:10:21,980 --> 00:10:25,040
 "Do you understand what I've done for you?" he asked them.

211
00:10:25,040 --> 00:10:27,100
 "You call me teacher and Lord, and rightly so,

212
00:10:27,100 --> 00:10:28,980
 "for that is what I am.

213
00:10:28,980 --> 00:10:32,620
 "Now that I, your Lord and teacher, have washed your feet,

214
00:10:32,620 --> 00:10:36,680
 "you also should wash one another's feet.

215
00:10:36,680 --> 00:10:40,380
 "I have set an example that you should do

216
00:10:40,380 --> 00:10:42,200
 "as I have done for you.

217
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:46,080
 "Very truly I tell you, no servant is greater

218
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:48,740
 "than his master, nor is a messenger greater

219
00:10:48,740 --> 00:10:51,180
 "than the one who sent him.

220
00:10:51,180 --> 00:10:52,580
 "Now that you know these things,

221
00:10:52,580 --> 00:10:57,580
 "you will be blessed if you do them."

222
00:10:57,580 --> 00:11:03,660
 Jesus, I pray against the spirit of familiarity tonight.

223
00:11:03,660 --> 00:11:09,820
 And use me and use your word

224
00:11:09,820 --> 00:11:13,000
 to give us a fresh glimpse of your greatness,

225
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:19,460
 your sacrifice and what you've done for us.

226
00:11:20,820 --> 00:11:24,660
 May it blow a fresh wind in our sails.

227
00:11:24,660 --> 00:11:29,360
 We pray this in Jesus' name, we all say, amen.

228
00:11:29,360 --> 00:11:35,020
 I'm gonna bring three points, is that okay with y'all?

229
00:11:35,020 --> 00:11:38,620
 Jesus knew some stuff.

230
00:11:38,620 --> 00:11:42,100
 That's not a point, I don't know why you're laughing.

231
00:11:42,100 --> 00:11:44,980
 It kind of hurts my feelings, but point number one,

232
00:11:44,980 --> 00:11:46,900
 Jesus knew stuff, write it down.

233
00:11:46,900 --> 00:11:47,740
 No, I'm kidding.

234
00:11:49,220 --> 00:11:54,220
 But the phrase that really got me was not what he did.

235
00:11:54,220 --> 00:11:55,980
 Okay, there's a few words.

236
00:11:55,980 --> 00:11:59,380
 In verse one, it says he knew something.

237
00:11:59,380 --> 00:12:02,060
 In verse two, it says he knew something.

238
00:12:02,060 --> 00:12:04,700
 And in verse four, he did something.

239
00:12:04,700 --> 00:12:07,920
 So he got up from the meal.

240
00:12:07,920 --> 00:12:10,180
 So John is helping us understand

241
00:12:10,180 --> 00:12:14,120
 what Jesus was thinking about before he did something.

242
00:12:14,120 --> 00:12:17,740
 Okay, and I've got a working title.

243
00:12:17,740 --> 00:12:18,940
 I don't know if it's gonna stick or not,

244
00:12:18,940 --> 00:12:21,060
 but it's "The Quest for Success."

245
00:12:21,060 --> 00:12:23,460
 Anybody wanna be successful up in here?

246
00:12:23,460 --> 00:12:26,780
 Okay, we need more ambition from the people at the porch.

247
00:12:26,780 --> 00:12:28,740
 Anybody actually wanna be successful?

248
00:12:28,740 --> 00:12:30,300
 Can be honest, it's okay.

249
00:12:30,300 --> 00:12:32,720
 Yeah, by the way, if you wanna date somebody,

250
00:12:32,720 --> 00:12:33,860
 you should have raised your hand

251
00:12:33,860 --> 00:12:35,460
 because girls aren't looking for guys

252
00:12:35,460 --> 00:12:37,300
 that don't wanna succeed in life.

253
00:12:37,300 --> 00:12:39,940
 Can I get amen from the ladies?

254
00:12:39,940 --> 00:12:43,100
 Let me ask again, anybody wanna be successful?

255
00:12:43,100 --> 00:12:46,060
 Okay, okay, my guy, you went too hard on that.

256
00:12:46,060 --> 00:12:48,620
 That looked desperate, all right?

